A previously published methodology for automatic tracking was used to detect deep fascia displacement in the MG (Fig. 1c) [2]. From the automatically selected pixels to be used in tracking, the Euclidean distance (d) was calculated between the positions in time (t), (ptx, pty) and in the initial frame (p0x, p0y).\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
